- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely, as the paper proposes different algorithms for solving the problem of minimizing block crossings. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant, as the problem can be formulated as a satisfiability problem, which is a topic in discrete mathematics. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is less likely, but still possible, as the paper mentions the use of SAT solvers, which are commonly used in AI applications. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is also a possibility, as the paper deals with visual representations of storylines.
